Re: Is safe running bitcoins with the same wallet on more computers
simultaneously?

Bitcointalk

2010-11-28 18:06:39 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Quote
   Will it be synchronized automatically?
   Very much not.  Using multiple copies of wallet.dat is not recommended
   or supported, in fact all of Bitcoin is designed to defeat that.  Both
   copies will get screwed up.
   If youʼre trying to consolidate your generated coins into one wallet, a
   better solution now is to run getwork miners on the additional systems.
    jgarzik has a CPU miner, and it supports tcatmʼs 4-way SSE2, so on
   Windows itʼs up to twice as fast as the built-in SHA if you have an AMD
   or recent Intel (core 3, 5 or 7).
   New demonstration CPU miner available:
   [12]http://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1925.0
